I'm a postmate and doordash delivery courier. This location has horrible management. There were multiple delivery courier's outside waiting, and some of their pickup orders were already done and ready to go. The security guard only let in 6 people max. There was no one dealing with delivery courier pickups separate from online customers pickups. It was one person dealing with everyone and it was bad. I had to wait outside for 20 minutes. Then when I got inside the food I was to pick up was old. So I had to wait for them to prepare it again. That's was another 30 minutes. Delivery couriers do get an hourly wage we get payed by a quota. So if we wait for 40-50 minutes at one restaurant that one delivery becomes our hourly wage. And most of the time it is only worth $3-$5. The only good thing was the staff member that was helping everyone. He kept his cool and helped everyone as fast as possible. This location was over run with orders and had poor leadership. I will avoid this location from now on, especially on the weekends.

My husband and I visited this location on their second day of opening, March 14th to be exact. I was due to have a c section in the morning and we wanted to get a good meal since we’d be in the hospital for the next 3 days. I get that they just had opened but the service was horrible... we’ve eaten at other locations multiple times and have never had such bad service. We witnessed multiple burritos rip and be thrown out into the garbage. They didn’t have white rice and when I requested it one of the staff mumbled angrily and responded with it will be ready when it’s ready to the one preparing my food. My husband asked the girl making his bowl to add extra steak which has never been a problem before I mean if we have to pay extra so be it but give us what we ask for.. she rolled her eyes and he gave her a look of are you serious right now and then she adjusted her ignorant face real quick. People had to skip one another because certain condiments weren’t available and it was just a mess overall. I haven’t been back since but I hope they got it together because I love chipotle and I am a frequent patient at the hospital across the street. Hopefully the staff will be better trained and taught some manners! Also the steak and shredded pork had no flavor which is disappointing especially since your paying a good amount of money for quality food.
